abstract: >-
  This technical note introduces Canonical Trajectory Governance (CTG), an AIKernel governance theory for admitting stochastic LLM-generated candidate actions into deterministic operating-system control. CTG evaluates each action through Logos, Ethos, and Pathos councils, gives Ethos canonical veto authority, and defines trajectory validity as the product of step-level gates. The paper also clarifies that the earlier AIKernel.RH prime-phase line should be referred to as the AIKernel Prime-Phase Model (PPM), not as a formal SH theory name.
